The paper discusses the representation of temporal knowledge using probabilistic networks, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of auxiliary nodes and instrumental variables to represent different kinds of relations between dates suggests a focus on structured inference (cs.SI) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the discussion of learning quantitative specifications from data suggests a possible connection to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
